  <RulesElement name="Ring of Flanking (paragon tier)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_TIV_MAGIC_ITEM_10045_20" source="Buck-A-Batch Magic Rings" revision-date="12/14/2010 10:35 AM">
    <Flavor> This wooden band has the carved image of an orc's head at its center with a sword on either side. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 14 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 21000 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Ring </specific>
    <specific name="Tier"/>
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID"/>
    <specific name="Armor"/>
    <specific name="Weapon"/>
    <specific name="Item Slot"> Ring </specific>
    <specific name="Requirement"/>
    <specific name="Critical"/>
    <specific name="Special"/>
    <specific name="Power"> Power (Daily): Free Action. Close burst 6. Choose up to 3 enemy targets within range. You create a phantom warrior in an empty space adjacent to each target. These warriors count as allies to you and your party for the purpose of granting a flanking bonus. Creatures can move through the phantoms or even end their turn in their space. If a phantom is on an occupied square it slides towards you, stopping on the next empty square it encounters. The phantoms remain until the end of the encounter.
